SUMMARY:Park Winters Garden Tour
DESCRIPTION:Park Winters is surrounded by hundreds of acres of farmland with unobstructed views of the Berryessa Blue Ridge Reserve. Originally planted in 1865\, our gardens take you back in time—now lovingly curated\, manicured and maintained. \nJoin us for a guided tour\, take in the beauty of 150 year old trees and stroll through our sunken garden filled with lavender and snowy white roses. The classic cypress trees soar and native songbirds call as we experience the scents and scenes of the western Yolo County countryside. This experience is approximately a 90 minute walking tour\, \n*Garden Tours are on the 2nd and 4th Saturday’s of each month\, with exception for July – August\, when we take a pause due to high temperatures – Garden Tours will resume in September.
URL:https://visityolo.com/event/park-winters-garden-tour/2026-06-06/
LOCATION:Park Winters\, Park Winters\, 27850 County Road 26 Winters\, CA 95694
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://visityolo.com/wp-content/uploads/ParkWinters2020_WM-5-1.jpg
END:VEVENT
